Now turn to implementing compute_score. To compute the score of a word, you need to know the point value of each letter in the word. You can associate letters and their point values with an array. Imagine an array of 26 ints, called POINTS, in which the first number is the point value for ‚ÄòA‚Äô, the second number is the point value for ‚ÄòB‚Äô, and so on. By declaring and initializing such an array outside of any single function, you can ensure this array is accessible to any function, including compute_score.
