Implement hash
Complete the hash function. hash should take a string, word, as input and return a positive (‚Äúunsigned‚Äù) int.
The hash function given to you returns an int between 0 and 25, inclusive, based on the first character of word. However, there are many ways to implement a hash function beyond using the first character (or characters) of a word. Consider a hash function that uses a sum of ASCII values or the length of a word. A good hash function reduces ‚Äúcollisions‚Äù and has a (mostly!) even distribution across hash table ‚Äúbuckets‚Äù.
